      <h4 id="Player">2. The player</h4>

      <p>In the second section, totally optional, you can define a player. This is an important step as the data you define here will be available in the learning analytics page, but you will also need to provide the engine with this data when starting a gameplay. You can define as many parameters as you want but there are only a limited number of types available, they are detailed on the table bellow.</p>

      <div class="bnfContainer">
        <pre class="pre-scrollable">player ::= 'Player' 
  ( Identifier ':' Type )+
'End'

Type ::= 'String' | 'Int' | 'Char' | 'Bool' | 'Float' | 'Text'</pre>

